{"nodes": [{"id": "draft_journey_draft5_1_full", "label": "Draft 5.1 Full Spec", "file_type": "document", "source_file": "draft-journey\\draft5.1-full.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Latest attribution-era canonical spec; adds Mythic/Loihi/IBM positioning (\u00a71.5), explicit biological inheritance (\u00a71.4), the \u00a720 campaign; superseded by draft 6.0 (missing-sign collapse)."}, {"id": "draft_journey_draft5_1_full_scap", "label": "Scap (atom of storage)", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "draft-journey\\draft5.1-full.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Holds one synapse weight: magnitude as analog charge on a capacitor, sign as a digital SRAM bit. A Scap is a WIRE not a neuron - its current history already encodes pre x post. The only name surviving draft 1 -> draft 6."}, {"id": "draft_journey_draft5_1_full_ganglion", "label": "Ganglion (atom of computation)", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "draft-journey\\draft5.1-full.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Hardwired 2-3-3-2 feedforward, 29 Scaps; abstracts one biological axon's multi-synapse behavior; 36 paths/29 scaps optimizes path-diversity-per-scap. Superseded as the atom in draft 6."}, {"id": "draft_journey_draft5_1_full_column", "label": "Column (sequential composition)", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "draft-journey\\draft5.1-full.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "A chain of Ganglia connected by learnable translate ALUs, with global capacitors holding transient state between steps."}, {"id": "draft_journey_draft5_1_full_lobe", "label": "Lobe (multi-branch DAG)", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "draft-journey\\draft5.1-full.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Composes Columns as a DAG (multi-parent, skip connections); the unit of brain region; Cortex Lobe and Hippocampus Lobe are the two main Lobes."}, {"id": "draft_journey_draft5_1_full_limbic_loop", "label": "Limbic Loop (recurrent two-timescale)", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "draft-journey\\draft5.1-full.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Top-level recurrent prediction loop: Cortex (fast) + Hippocampus (slow) connected by a Commissure; decay factor mandatory for stability."}, {"id": "draft_journey_draft5_1_full_brainstem", "label": "Brainstem (central controller)", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "draft-journey\\draft5.1-full.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "The only central controller: computes loss, broadcasts pulse-width shares + tri-state sign, manages clocks/gating; ~8-15k transistors; not a CPU, not a backprop engine."}, {"id": "draft_journey_draft5_1_full_commissure", "label": "Commissure (inter-Lobe connector)", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "draft-journey\\draft5.1-full.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "A small group of learnable Ganglia connecting Cortex<->Hippocampus; trains slow (every M clocks) to give both Lobes a stable reference; natural home for Synaptic Drift."}, {"id": "draft_journey_draft5_1_full_special_generalist", "label": "SpecialGeneralist (gated Ganglion reuse)", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "draft-journey\\draft5.1-full.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "A Generalist Ganglion reused under context masks from Specialist Ganglia; gains capacity per Scap without hardware; gated-off Scaps register zero contribution (falls out of the diffusion math)."}, {"id": "draft_journey_draft5_1_full_attribution_based_hierarchical_diffusion", "label": "Attribution-Based Hierarchical Diffusion", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "draft-journey\\draft5.1-full.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "The draft-5-era learning rule: loss broadcasts from the top and diffuses down, each level splitting its share in proportion to stored child contributions (|a.W| measured for free), landing at Scaps as a PWM pulse in six clocks. Attribution (proportion) not gradient (sensitivity). Died in draft 6: it carried magnitude but never DIRECTION."}, {"id": "draft_journey_draft5_1_full_distribution_measurement", "label": "Distribution measurement (time-to-threshold)", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "draft-journey\\draft5.1-full.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Each Scap's contribution is measured for free as time-to-threshold on a measurement cap (shorter time = stronger contribution); a ratio measurement robust to drift/temperature."}, {"id": "draft_journey_draft5_1_full_translate_alu", "label": "Translate ALU (learnable reshaping)", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "draft-journey\\draft5.1-full.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "A hardwired analog n->m matrix-multiply with learnable Scaps that reshapes signal between Ganglia; catalog of sizes fixed at fabrication."}, {"id": "draft_journey_draft5_1_full_loss_conservation", "label": "Loss conservation invariant", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "draft-journey\\draft5.1-full.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Each level satisfies sum(shares_to_children)=parent_loss; a system-wide invariant used to bug-check the simulation piece by piece; holds under multi-parent by summing shares."}, {"id": "draft_journey_draft5_1_full_two_timescale_cortex_hippocampus", "label": "Two-timescale Cortex/Hippocampus", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "draft-journey\\draft5.1-full.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Same topology, different update cadence: Cortex fast (every clock), Hippocampus slow (every k clocks); their difference is the prediction error - the predictive-coding pattern; a re-derivation of Complementary Learning Systems, carried into draft 6 as sleep + LUT."}, {"id": "draft_journey_draft5_1_full_resident_weight_cim", "label": "Resident-weight / compute-in-memory (CIM)", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "draft-journey\\draft5.1-full.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Weights never leave the substrate during operation; storage and compute are the same hardware; only inputs/labels enter, only predictions leave. The project's committed substrate property (broader field = CIM)."}, {"id": "draft_journey_draft5_1_full_four_properties", "label": "The four substrate properties", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "draft-journey\\draft5.1-full.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Online, sparse, continuous, resident-weight - the four properties the substrate must make the cheap path; survived every pivot unchanged."}, {"id": "draft_journey_draft5_1_full_neuromorphic_positioning", "label": "Neuromorphic positioning (Mythic/Loihi/IBM)", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "draft-journey\\draft5.1-full.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Positioning vs existing CIM/neuromorphic: Mythic (inference-only, frozen weights), Loihi (digital spikes, local-Hebbian), IBM analog (gradient-descent needs weight-transport); the distinguishing claim = continuous + on-chip learning + hierarchical + local-measurement."}], "edges": [{"source": "draft_journey_draft5_1_full", "target": "draft_journey_draft5_0", "relation": "conceptually_related_to", "confidence": "INFERRED", "confidence_score": 0.85, "source_file": "draft-journey\\draft5.1-full.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "draft_journey_draft5_1_full_attribution_based_hierarchical_diffusion", "target": "draft_journey_draft5_1_full_distribution_measurement", "relation": "conceptually_related_to", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "draft-journey\\draft5.1-full.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "draft_journey_draft5_1_full", "target": "draft_journey_draft5_1_full_scap", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "draft-journey\\draft5.1-full.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "draft_journey_draft5_1_full", "target": "draft_journey_draft5_1_full_ganglion", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "draft-journey\\draft5.1-full.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "draft_journey_draft5_1_full", "target": "draft_journey_draft5_1_full_column", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "draft-journey\\draft5.1-full.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "draft_journey_draft5_1_full", "target": "draft_journey_draft5_1_full_lobe", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "draft-journey\\draft5.1-full.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "draft_journey_draft5_1_full", "target": "draft_journey_draft5_1_full_limbic_loop", 